Hi Mike,

You are welcome to use my skeletal, which I've attached below. PeerJ will probably accept your oversized manuscript, but they will also charge you extra for it (the Lori paper had quite a bit of extra publishing cost tacked on to it due to length, and I'm assuming you are talking about a longer paper). And because of how the system is set up the exact cost is generally not known up until your paper is otherwise ready to be published, at which point you are sort of over a barrel.

Anyhow, I am glad to hear you are getting the Archbishop manuscript ready to publish, cheers!

-Scott



